Only bought their dim sum, and it was edible and decently priced. However, the price charged is not what is displayed. Happen on 2 of my visits. Would not patronise again due to this dishonest business practice.
Good, cheap, quiet. Coffee is decent, I like the fried bee hoon which is sweetish version and harder to find.
The food is delicious and the price is reasonable. Coffee and tea are also provided here, and breakfast, lunch and dinner are provided.
